Mean percentage recoveries were calculated for the studied medications, confirming the accuracy of the proposed approach; furthermore, the % found for raw materials and dosage forms was compared to the data gathered by the comparative methods [7,18]. The student t-test and the Variance Ratio F-test were employed to compare the outcomes of the comparison and proposed approach, as shown in Table 2
                           . The tabulated results of the t-test and F-test show that there was no discernible difference between the two approaches [34] illustrating the accuracy and precision of the suggested approach. Intra and inter-day precisions were calculated for the studied drugs to assess the precision of the suggested strategy by utilizing three concentrations of each of MIN and TIM, with three replicates of each concentration (Table 3
                           ). The %RSD values were less than 2 %, which indicates that the suggested strategy is precise.
